  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "Gouqizi is a sweet, neutral herb that enters the liver, kidneys and lungs. In English it is known as Wolfberry. It is used for nourishing and tonifying the liver and kidneys, benefiting the essence, brightening the eyes, enriching the yin, nourishing blood and moistening the lungs.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "枸杞子味甘，藥性平，歸屬肝、腎二經，能明目補肝腎。主治肝腎不足，腰酸遺精，頭暈目眩，視力減退，消渴等，屬於常用的食療中藥。\n",
    "zh-Hans": "枸杞子味甘，药性平，歸属肝、肾二经，能明目补肝肾。主治肝肾不足，腰酸遺精，头暈目眩，視力減退，消渴等，属于常用的食疗中药。\n"
  },
  "tcmModernResearch": {
    "en": "An aqueous extract of Frustus Lycii has been found to enhance non-specific immunity and relieve liver damage in mice. It also contains carotene which is important for good eyesight.\n",
